# Copy to .env.local for local development, and set the same variable in your
# host's environment settings for production.

# Where both lead forms POST their JSON payload.
# Until this is set, the forms validate normally but show an honest
# "preview mode" notice instead of pretending the request was delivered.
#
# Easiest option: create a free form at https://formspree.io and paste its
# endpoint here. Any URL that accepts a JSON POST works (CRM webhook,
# Zapier/Make catch hook that emails you + appends to a Google Sheet, etc.).
#
# Payload shape:
#   { kind: "lunch-request" | "restaurant-partner", ...fields, receivedAt, source }
NEXT_PUBLIC_FORM_ENDPOINT=
